This solution is based on recursion. Here a recursive function "removenode" is used. The end of the linked list is reached with the help of the recursive function. 
![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/a95d85b9-4549-4960-a10a-5f6614b0dd0a_1664804128.6790764.png)

Let us take the above image for illustration. The target value is 6. 
1. When the end of the linked list is reached by recursive function and NULL is found(The base case) then that instance/stack of the function will return NULL to the previous node's function call.
2. Here the value of the node before NULL is 6 which is equal to the target, if this is the case then that function stack will not return the current pointer to the previous node but the pointer to the NULL, Thus losing the pointer of node containing 6.
3. When the node 2 is reached then the condition is checked, if its equal to target or not, In this case, it is not thus the current node's next will become the returned node from the previous function stack which was NULL. Thus next of two will become NULL. 
4. When 6 is reached, the condition evalues as true and and thus returns the pointer of (2) to the previous node.
5. When 1 reaches the, condition evaluates as false and thus the next of 1 is the returned pointer which is 2.


```
ListNode *removenode(ListNode *ptr, int target){
	//base case
    if(ptr==NULL){
        return NULL;
    }
	//call the recursive function and pass the next node
    ListNode *returnnode = removenode(ptr->next,target);
	///All the below lines will be executed when the recursive function comes back
	//check if the value of cuurent node is equal to the value of target.
    if(ptr->val == target){
		//if the value of current node is equal to the taget then return the previously returned value.
        return returnnode;
    }
    else{
		//since the value of current node is not equal to target thus modify the next node.
        ptr->next = returnnode;
		//return the pointer to the current node.
        return ptr;
    }
}
class Solution {
public:
    ListNode* removeElements(ListNode* head, int val) {
        return removenode(head,val);
    }
};
```

